## Implementation Order

**Total timeline: ~4 weeks** (not 12 days — see lessons from testing)

### Phase 0: Clean slate (week 1)

- Trace all import chains. Identify which modules depend on which.
- Write dependency diagram to verify no circular imports.
- Remove deprecated modules confirmed unused:
  - `bandit.py` → inline 30 lines into `learning.py`
  - `activation.py` → inline scoring into `graph.py`
  - `conditions.py`, `reasoning.py`, `simulate.py`, `utils.py` → remove (dead code)
  - `maintenance.py` → rewrite as telemetry sync thread only
  - `self_tune.py` → remove (bandit in learning.py sufficient)
  - `tree.py`, `read.py` (except `update_state`) → inline or remove
  - `embedding.py` → keep fallback (FTS5) but remove optional fastembed dependency
  - `estimator.py`, `export.py` → inline into handler logic
  - `analytics.py`, `graph_ops.py`, `insight_propagation.py`, `resolve.py` → keep or merge
- Remove handlers: `export_handler.py`, `complete_handler.py`
- Remove prompts: `feature-plan`
- Update schema: add `routes`, `route_phases` tables
- Add `archived` column to `routes`
- Rename tools to `plan`, `checkpoint`, `review`, `manage`

### Phase 1: Core loop (week 2)

- `plan` — single route from goal decomposition + mesh alternatives
- `checkpoint` — phase completion with immutable baseline deviation
- `checkpoint` — status-check mode (route_id only)
- `checkpoint` — outcome derivation (success/partial/failure)
- `checkpoint` — evidence verification (replaces separate verify)
- `checkpoint` — terminal phase handling (route_completed)
- `manage` — revert, set_cursor, delete (3 sub-actions only)
- `manage` — archive (completed route lifecycle)

### Phase 2: Learning + sync (week 3)

- `review` — session retrospective with deviations
- `review` — learnings mined from checkpoints
- `review` — mesh_status (only place sync health appears)
- Checkpoint sync thread (background, every 5 min)
- Degraded mode: buffer checkpoints locally when Mesh unreachable
- Mesh baseline import on server start
- `openplan://sync-status` resource
- Outcome aggregation in Mesh (success_rate)

### Phase 3: Mesh + business (week 4)

- Mesh API: `POST /checkpoints`, `GET /baselines`
- GitHub OAuth device code flow
- Polar billing integration
- Personal baselines (Starter feature)
- Team-private baselines (Team feature)
- Dynamic `agent_loop` prompt
- Error messages with traceback context

### Phase 4: Launch (end of week 4)

- Test suite: 166+ tests passing
- MCP registry: `mcp install openplan-mcp`
- Homebrew: `brew install anomalyco/tap/openplan`
- Smithery: `uvx openplan-mcp`
- Docs: opencode.ai/docs/openplan (1 page)

